nodes.label: Geometric Data
nodes.title: Data regarding size, shape, and other relevant information of an object, represented in 3D.

nodes.label: Geospatial Data
nodes.title: Data revolving around a specific location in the real world, e.g. GIS data.

nodes.label: Sensor data
nodes.title: Data acquired from sensors, e.g. temperature.

nodes.label: Historical Data
nodes.title: Data regarding previous events about a subject.

nodes.label: Process Data
nodes.title: Data generated during system operation, e.g. real-time data.

nodes.label: Simulation Data
nodes.title: Data generated from computer simulations, e.g. fluid dynamics simulation.

nodes.label: Metadata
nodes.title: Data providing additional information about other data, e.g. file format or source.

nodes.label: Landscape data
nodes.title: Information about characteristics of a specific geographic area, e.g. vegetation or rainfall.

nodes.label: Biotic data
nodes.title: Data involving living organisms, e.g. plants, bacteria, and human beings.

nodes.label: Abiotic Data
nodes.title: Data involving nonliving that affect organisms, e.g. climate, water, and atmosphere.

nodes.label: Dashboard Visualization
nodes.title: A collection of two-dimensional visualization techniques.

requirements_and_challenges.Real-Time: Processing data within milliseconds, by means of low latency or data compression.
requirements_and_challenges.Network Connectivity: Connection to the network using Bluetooth, Wi-Fi, or another method.
requirements_and_challenges.Computing Power: Ability to support computation load without significant performance loss.
requirements_and_challenges.Data Capacity: Ability to store all (generated) data, locally or in the cloud.
requirements_and_challenges.Integration: Seamless integration of data, software, or similar component into the system.
requirements_and_challenges.Security: Securing the system by means of ensuring privacy, integrity, encryption, authentication, or using blockchain.
requirements_and_challenges.Continuous Improvement: Ability to analyze data from the model or system in order to make decisions for improvements, using simulations or human intervention.
requirements_and_challenges.Reliability: Behaviour system operates as defined over a period of time.
requirements_and_challenges.Accuracy: Representation of the model or system with enough accuracy.
requirements_and_challenges.Obtrusiveness: Ease of perception of the system for the human eye by using dashboards, 3D models, or other methods.
requirements_and_challenges.Granularity: Ability to see different viewpoints of the model or system, with different levels of detail.
requirements_and_challenges.Standardization: Alignment in understanding between different domains, stakeholders, or goals.
requirements_and_challenges.Economic Value: Demonstrating the business or monetary value of the system.
requirements_and_challenges.Safety: Protection from risks for humans by verification or issuing certificates.
requirements_and_challenges.Collaboration: Ability for multiple stakeholders to make adjustments to the system or model.

assessment.Suitable: The tool fulfills the requirement or challenge without additional effort.
assessment.Moderately Suitable: The tool fulfills the requirement or challenge, but within specific terms and/or requires extra effort to be fulfilled.
assessment.Unsuitable: The tool does not fulfill the requirement or challenge, or requires huge amounts of effort to be fulfilled.
assessment.Blank: The requirement or challenge is not applicable to be assessed by the visualization tool.
